<p>I have an input text and an empty label in html</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="form-group"&gt;     &lt;label for="hsDetailsForm-name"&gt;Denumire&lt;/label&gt;     &lt;input id="hsDetailsForm-name" type="text" class="form-control" ng-model="hydroStation.name" placeholder="Obligatoriu" required ng-blur="validationObliga()" autofocus/&gt;     &lt;label id="obliga"&gt;&lt;/label&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and here is the function in js</p>  <pre><code>$scope.validationObliga = function () {     var value = $.trim($("hsDetailsForm-name").val());      if (value == "") {         $('#obliga').html("Campul este obligatoriuu!").css("color", "red");     } else {         $('#obliga').html("");     } } </code></pre>  <p><code>ng-blur</code> works and when empty it writes "Campul este obligatoriuu!" in red, however when you type something in the text field and focus out of it, it still says that, it doesnt change the label to "". Why don't it go in the else ?</p>